values: Ok. I made a new account. I'm not gonna use this one anymore. This one's stupid and stuff. My new LJ can be located under the name kingofclutch, so add me as a friend. sorry i've made your life hard. it happens, doesnt it?

Gerard Project.........or Game 7? So here's what's gonna happen: if i choose to work on my project during game 7 of the Pistons - Cavaliers series, LeBron James is probably gonna make history by like coming from down by like 40 points to win the game in three overtimes with stats like 74 points, 16 rebounds, 14 assists, 9 steals, and 5 blocks. i would cry. eternally. OK. so let's say i decide to watch the game. I fail to complete the project and LeBron has a terrible game and gets destroyed by the team that should've ended this series three games ago. pros and cons, pros and cons............i guess i'll do the project..........its a harder choice than you'd think.

i'm a little behind. on tonight's agenda:

1. Finish Project 5 and edit Project 3
2. Do Chapter notes for Fast Food Nation

OK. that doesnt appear to be much, but it is enough to keep me up, if i want to make a good grade, that is. AND I DO. so there
i'm too friggin lazy to type that much. but if you're a senior, you know who you are. and i found out today that patience indeed is a virtue. a nice one indeed.

this year really, really, really, really, really sucked. like hard. almost unbearably hard. everyone of any importance to me last year is no longer here. my grades sucked. my life sucked. fortunately, i have momentum going into next year. good grades + good changes = potentially great finish = potentially great start next year. it's almost dinner, but when i get back, i'm gonna leave something for those who i haven't and those i wont see next year. i apologize in advance for the length of my next entry.

The worst week of the year is upon us...........I have made a schedule that, if followed, should make this week more tolerable. Here is a list of assignments by class:
(the number following represents the assignment's amount of time consumination on a 1-10 scale)

History - restaurant project (9), speech paper (3)
Church History - Final (2)
Weight Training - Final (.000001)
Mythology - Final (2)
Chemistry - Final (9)
Graphic Design - Projects (7)

It's simple. Three things on my summer checklist:

1) Relax
2) Summer Job
3) Play basketball

Once I get back, I'll be ready to take on my final year here. Here are my goals:

1) One B per term at most. All A's if possible. Next year will not be a repeat of this year.
2) Get accepted to one of three colleges: Baylor U., Austin C., Tulsa U. Midwest colleges kick ass.
3) Play basketball.
4) Enjoy as much of next year as possible.

Yo, sound the bell. School is in session, suckers.
i got my tux'n stuff yesterday, so now i's ready to go............it's time, right about that time.

2 more: caldy and chemistry. B-/C+ on chem, so that's okay, and i'm just not gonna worry about josh.......so we got, what, five down? yeah, five. tonight, i will make arby's progress and eventually the seniority thing will unfold. the longer i have to wait, the more doubtful i become. i'm really doubting my appointability right now. whatever. after those two, it's all about the prom. good god, the prom.
corsage? check. project #2? done. project #3? yep. three down, nine to go. chem test tomorrow, and soon enough i'll know whether or not i was appointed.
gerard's test was MATCHING!!!!!!!! one down, eleven to go. i think i'll get at least four more today.

i've still yet to complete anything. i didnt get a corsage and i didnt finish my graphic design project. hopefully i was appointed to seniority. that would really get the proverbial ball rolling. i'm crossing my fingers.
update. i am gonna be up all night. let's see what i can do tonight.

things are looking as up now as they possibly could be. so i am going to be thankful and work from here. i have work that i need to do, but as long as i can get it done, all is well. i'm gonna try to get up early so i can read and get the reading stuff over with, then i have graphic design to do, followed by studying for chemistry. i think i can get off my ass and get things done over the next 3.5 weeks........i just need to stay happy. i'm preparing for prom, so it gives me a reason to be happy until may 6th, and then theres that day. i really need for that to go well. i just need to get through it, it doesn't have to be the time of my life, though if it ended up being closer to that (which is possible but kind of doubtful), i'd be muchly merry for the final 2 weeks and probably for most of the summer. i refuse to allow bad things to happen, and for those i can't stop, i refuse to let them get to me. i just need people here for me and work to keep me busy. i can worry during the summer, because the day i get back in August, i'm pretty sure i'll be quite alright. thanks.

today was ok. i'm not really content, but this is the best i can get until next year, so i have to work with this. i hope next year will be more like my sophomore year. and i hope Ben Gordon can beat the Heat.

what a long drive. it was so easy though. thats what you get for doubting me, father. so, yeah. did i mention Ben Gordon's a pretty good long range shooter? because he is. SPECIAL PROJECTS WEEK!!!!!! i think i've covered everything.....prom is closer, but i talk about that in every entry. i think i should talk about Ben Gordon in every entry from now on, even though no person who might read this will care. Ben G. is the shizzy.

i can definitely say this has been the best break this year. i got my haircut, my dad gave me some courses in "roadside saurvival training", and i saw the best basketball game in a long time last night. Ben Gordon tied the record for most consecutive 3pt shots made, making 9 out of 9. good god that was awesome. my brother made 5 in a row in a game one time. speaking of my brother, we got in a fight because he made a very not-good comment about my date to the prom. when i tell any member of my family the name of my date, they ask me the dumbest questions. my dad asked me if she spoke english and my brother asked me if i was gonna wear a turban to the prom(?). bunch of redneck bastards. cant wait till my brother comes down to move me out. that oughtta be fun.................
i'm kind of scared right now...........i fear i may have made an unintelligent decision.........i really hope i get a phone call tonight.

i got that over with *sigh* why couldn't i do it earlier? it doesn't matter, because now i have a date to the prom. let's all be happy ::throws random confetti, screams at top of lungs, eats the cake, high fives Danny, starts 'The Wave'::

a win-win situation? i can't lose those, can I? man i really messed during the junior trip. i only have a good time at amusement park when i'm with my family, which is odd. i cant enjoy my life when i'm around them, and i love life around my friends. how odd. anyway, i still have work to do. maybe tonight................
school. better than home, but still.......
so slow.......so painful......someone get me away from here.......i'm gonna die soon if no one comes and whisks me away to school.............please........sooooooooo boooooooorrrrrrrrrrrrred.

the longe i stay here, the sicker i get. my throat feels like crap, and i have a friggin headache. but it's thursday, less than a week away. i just have to hold out a little bit longer..........damn this cold, wet weahther, and damn whoever drank the rest of the OJ........DAMNS IT!!!!!!

i'm ready to go back to school. can't wait until the junior trip, and i'm already making plans for prom, because i'm not about to have another winter formal on my hands..............is it only monday? damn.
i can do nothing right. it's how things usually end up, and to no surprise, it's happened again. my bad......

i sacrifice my opinion, my beliefs, my feelings. i do so to keep from stepping on anyone's toes, to keep them happy. too bad it makes me feel terrible in the end. i told i was alright with what she said, and i was, at the time. only because i made myself feel okay about it. i can't change how she feels, therefore i try to change the way i feel. it works both ways; i can't change how i feel. i can mask it, yes, but change it i can't. i couldn't tell her what i really thought, and now i know i need to, no matter what she says back. all of this, just in time for finals. yay.
it didnt go the way i really wanted it to, but this should lead to interesting conversations. give me a little more time, if you dont mind.

i'm doing it tonight, because if i don't, my heart will explode. i'm so nervous, but i know this should have been done about a week ago. when 9:00 rolls around, it'll be game time. this wont be the last entry for today. i'll have one for you at 10.

.........when's the next geekfest? oh my goodness, it was most definitely the best of the five i have under my belt. i can't wait until the next one. i just doubt any future one can beat this last one. yeah, it was THAT good.

damn, i'm sore. played football with the guys for some odd hours last night. but man do i feel great. this week has already started off fantastic. though some people need to understand that taking me seriously gonna cause them problems if they want to be friends with me. serious people are wierd. anyway, i'm actually gonna go to all of my classes for the first time in three class weeks. i must really be feeling good. Creed was right. i shouldn't listen to those that i thought were more intelligent than i, and i was trying too hard. i found that out pretty quickly today. i feel like posterizing someone. hook em horns. i totally forgot the longhorns won. man, this school has stripped me of my personality. business needs to pick up again, and i can't think of a better time to do so.

for someone who gives such good advice, joel sure can piss me off sometimes........its hard to argue with someone who just refuses to care about logic and what the world commonly sees as success. different people have different goals, different views, different dreams. sometimes they vary so much, arguments like that have to arise. i know what i want, theres no conflict in my mind as to where i want to be when i turn 25, 30, 45, 60. i used to get mad at my brother for not caring about school. for christ's sake he's 19 and still a junior! but when he told me what his plans for the future were, it hit me. he may not give a shit about being smart, popular, or rich, but he does give a shit about doing what he cares about the most, what makes him happy. so lets argue about all that junk, as long as it doesnt become an obstacle, i'm cool with it. wow.....i went from being pissed off to content after writing this entry.....nice.

my year is more like a few months......i'll post my first and last entry of my few months.

Sep:This turd next to me will not stop eating chips.
Sep:I love making these videos!!!!

Oct:Ok. So I'm gonna be New Orleans tomorrow. It is inanimate right?
Oct:i love kenneth. he is going to let me stay in his room tonight.

Nov:this is almost too upsetting........
Nov:big words are for big boys. joel......you win......for now....

Dec:if you are reading this, comment......
Dec:havent gotten there yet....

after several consecutive minutes of self-pity, i have recovered and now feel ready to start the week. but i do apologize for not being part of the group. i like groups of two to four much better. i can handle that many when i know the majority, which wasnt the case today. i was regretting it while i was doing it, but it wont change until i get to know all of the people i'm around. i know how i can, but thats only in an ideal situation. not to mention my way of doing so would more than likely prove to be a way that the others would not care for, but thats my pessimism kicking in. i just need to grow the balls to ask. meh. lets go for it. have good week peoples.

i can sum up my day so far with two words: simply refer to the senior section of the 2005 edition of the ASMS yearbook. look under Zach Gardner's name, and there you have it......."Well........crap." i'd say i tried, but there really is no "try". i just did not. great intentions, joel, as well as great expectations. with me tho, the more the merrier? not usually. disappointed? yeah. but that's it.this isnt me, so it wont last forever. quote of the day:
"Kickers shall not speak unless spoken to" ~ Ray Lewis, Baltimore Ravens
I'd make a great kicker.

good thing elise helped me rob that bank. I DONT NEED YOU, SANTA!!!! I GOT MONEY FOR MY OWN DAMN PRESENTS!!!!!

Inspiring, shining, rising
And when you're in my way
I'm not dividing me from you cause we're working together
Perfect in its splendor like the currents of the weather
The splinter in my center hindering all of my pleasure
Is me manifested as you in this endeavor
Once responsibility is taken I can render
Experience to be however I want to remember

Time and time again we fall in to the depths of who we are
But you can't keep running away from what you're trying to find

Put yourself through the scariest of scenarios
Enter experiences you normally wouldn't dare to go
It's all for the character and the arrogant afterglow
Of knowing it's appearance according to your patterns of growth
And what your parents handed down to you to handle
Make sure you carry torches when their puttin out your candles
Prediction can be unkind but unwind them still
Don't erase the part of you that's responsible for your will

Time and time again we fall into the depths of who we are
But you can't keep running away from what you're trying to find

Well I've seen you and those things you do
And the way you hide that shadow can't be good for you
Your dark defines your light

There's some utterly damaged particles to deal with
And if I stutter I'm sorry but it's hard to feel swift
When stuck in my stomach is a cannon ball anchor to lift
I've been pushing it down pretending it doesn't exist
Well this is what happens when you're pissed about being pissed
You dig yourself so deep you resist just to resist
And there's no way to get back experiences you missed
So start right now today and risk furiousness for bliss

teh formal was greatness. they screwed me on my platinum tie, but i lived without. had so much fun, makes me wonder why i worried so much about whether i would or not without a date. i moved my crap down here to niall's room. i'm not moving down here, unless tommy decides to not fix the port in my room, which is very likely. i'm finally gonna get myself an ipod so i wont be so damn bored during my trips. niall and i are going to taco bell to acquire more music that i cant find anywhere here. too bad limewire and the hot spot dont exactly mix. i feel great. almost like myself again. a few more steps and i'm there. have a great week everybody.
if you are reading this, comment.......becuase you all love me and would never not comment. let's go do stuff........

i think i like to take my problems, drive the fact that whatever it is is my fault, and then make things worse by taking my friends problems and dwelling on them until i "drive" myself insane. also, big words are for big boys. joel......you win......for now....
cool new pics on myspace..........the book i'm reading is absolute awesomness.......may dad said he may reconsider forcing me to go back to elkmont after christmas........yay

I want to stop bitching so bad, but i'm so frustrated right now, and i just want this issue to not exist. I've complained constantly about them and there's only one way i can solve it: by doing something. But when i have the chance, i dont, and now i cant just be myself. I can forget about the stupid things i've done, but when i'm around other people who know what i've done, it just lingers in the back of my mind and keeps me from being normal. And yes, my whole social problem thing now has to do with only like three or four girls here, but it aggrivates me soooooo damn much that i cant be Jake all the time. That was the reasoning behind wanting to ask certain people to the winter formal. but of course, if no one knows me, no one will want to go with me, right? all i have to do is strike one normal conversation with each of those that i am uncomfortable around and it would be all over. i just want to say i'm not wanted. unless someone says that, i really doubt that. when i'm comfortable around these people, my little circle of friends would be closed, complete enough for me to be content here. The way it was last year. Pardon me.................FFFFFUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUUCK!.......eventually i'll just say that.....fuck this......and then just start acting like the jake everyone remembers from last year. aside from all this.........i probably could use a really good friend of the opposite sex.........i want a girl in my life that is just my female equivalent of Niall, of Creed, of Joel even(?....i guess....). i need balance............maybe some Zolof or whatever the hell you call that stuff....."happy pills".......good day all........good day.........

if only i were ingorant to others' knowledge.......there would be like no pressure on me and things would be a lot easier........i guess.........or should i just not care what others think or know and be myself? wait its not like its an option, i cant be just ignorant...........well then. how do you not care about what others think about you? that is easily the #1 thing that keeps me from being content on a consistent basis.............all i need to do is break out of this for one minute and be myself for just a little while and i think that would do a world of good for me......i always picture myself doing it but when i'm in the situation to be myself i just do..............nothing. who knows? maybe someday i'll take a "risk" and be social, like it even is a risk..........

i have been so wound up and tight about everything. it wasnt like this back when i had sports to play. i would have a blah kind of week, ya know, a then we'd have that game at the end of the week. seems like they'd all be so close. i remember workin my ass of to get my part done, putting every ounce of adrenaline and emotion i had into it. i'd do it, and whether we won or lost, i felt so great those next few days. especially after a game that was so insane that it left people on thier knees, crying(yeah, it happened once). i wish i had the drive to do things the way i wanted to on that football field. i have way too much emotion and adrenaline and stuff to just sit here and talk about emotional stuff. i need to "play it out". i wonder if soccer could do that for me? i know i could pick it up easy, but it would have to be the kind of sport where i know my little actions make a difference. its easy for me to see that in football, notsomuch for soccer. meh.....i guess giving it a try would not hurt, tho i know i'm more for "hands" on sports, if you know what i mean.

k everyone................break is almost over, and i can actually say i cant wait to be back in mobile. stayed with dominick, and while i didnt have as much fun as a whole as expected, i had much more fun than i would have had, had i stayed here at home. i am more than ready to get this term rolling.......i think. before i leave to go back i have a couple of things to say i guess:

JOEL- i've missed you.........we can only hope there is still time for me to be philosophical and stuff
NIALL- if we cant get a second ethernet port, i will really push to move in you......or at least i may move compy to your room
::btw, if anyone likes Risk or cool games like that, get The Political Machine...yes niall, i'm getting it again::
JAMES- things dont seem the same as last year for some reason.....i'm sure it'll change once youve been here for a few weeks
ELISE- dom and i harassed each other about absolutely everything......i dont "like" you or anything like that, as much as i enjoyed listening to dom's reasoning (why i shouldnt "try"?) though
BEN- ::flying moose kick:: yeah, that felt good.
KYLE- diffcal sure is fun, isnt it? i know how much youre "struggling" in there.....i'm here for ya:)
SEAN- maybe sometime during the christmas break dominick and i can see you or something......i guess
EVERYONE- hope you all got your new year's resolutions planned.....can you believe it's already almost december? hope everyone had a fantastic thxgiving break...........HAPPY HOLIDAYS you guys:)
